<article class="block-one" id="case-studies">
<section class="inner">
<h2 class="page-name">Case Studies</h2>
<section class="case-studies-logos">
<img id="wikinger" src="http://www.richardpearsonmarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/wilkinger-e1376991526988.png" alt="Wikinger" />
<img id="greencore" src="http://www.richardpearsonmarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/aunt-bessie.png" alt="Aunt Bessie's" />
<img id="hain" src="http://www.richardpearsonmarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/natco.png" alt="NATCO" />
<img id="capri-sun" src="http://www.richardpearsonmarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/7-2-11-youngslogo_lg.png" alt="Young's Sea Food" />
<img id="premier-foods" src="http://www.richardpearsonmarketing.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/bakkavor.png" alt="Bakkavor" />
</section>
<article class="greencore-text"><p><strong>Client:</strong> Aunt Bessie&#8217;s</p>
<p><strong>Client Issue:</strong> Overall business strategy identified convenience sector as growth area and need to get a handle on &#8220;size of the prize&#8221; and requirements to deliver it.</p>
<p><strong>RPM Input:</strong> Developed a bespoke business plan format for the convenience sector, linked with internal sales team and analysed external data e.g. IGD/Kantar etc.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> Aligned Aunt Bessie&#8217;s products to convenience shopper missions to agree &#8220;core&#8221; range listing priorities and provided a sound rationale for a focused distribution drive.</p>
<p><strong>Testimonial:</strong> &#8220;He worked seamlessly with our marketing and commercial departments to produce some key strategies that have been invaluable to our business development within this channel.&#8221;</p>
</article><article class="hain-text"><p><strong>Client:</strong> Natco Foods Ltd</p>
<p><strong>Client Issue:</strong> Over reliant on ethnic independent outlets and unable to get the support of the major multiple supermarkets.</p>
<p><strong>RPM Input:</strong> Took on sales representation for major multiples for ethnic foods range, developed buying contacts for snacks, hot beverages &amp; ready meals. Secured listings for brand &amp; own label.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> &#8220;Sitar&#8221; snacks listing in Waitrose &amp; NISA, &#8220;NATCO&#8221; spiced tea listing in Sainsbury&#8217;s and Tesco O/L rice contract.</p>
<p><strong>Testimonial:</strong> &#8220;During this period Richard made some key distribution breakthroughs, which contributed to the significant growth of our business.&#8221;</p>
</article><article class="capri-sun-text"><p><strong>Client:</strong> Young&#8217;s Seafood</p>
<p><strong>Client Issue:</strong> Aim to become the definitive fish/seafood website having a wealth of material around the business but the need for someone to take on focus &amp; accountability to deliver project.</p>
<p><strong>RPM Input:</strong> Project-managed new website initiative, co-ordinating with all key internal personnel, liaising with external agencies and managing recipe podcast filming.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> Established blueprint for overall layout, unique hits more than trebled from 11K to 38K &amp; settled down at 25K per month.</p>
<p><strong>Testimonial:</strong> &#8220;I would recommend Richard to companies looking for an experienced, external resource, who is able to &#8216;hit the ground running&#8217; &amp; make a difference.&#8221;</p>
</article><article class="premier-foods-text"><p><strong>Client:</strong> Bakkavor Group Ltd</p>
<p><strong>Client Issue:</strong> Looking for more cost-effective approaches for their search process.</p>
<p><strong>RPM Input:</strong> Undertook search assignment for senior commercial role in a key business unit, built proper understanding of company culture &amp; requirements and used own personal food industry network to identify  best possible candidate.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> Only 1 candidate submitted with 4 from other sources.  Our candidate was successful.</p>
<p><strong>Testimonials:</strong><br />
&#8220;Richard used his extensive network and tenacious approach to deliver a great result in our search for a senior commercial appointment for our business.&#8221; &#8211; Client</p>
<p>&#8220;Richard provided invaluable support in sourcing the right next step for my career progression. He complemented this with his insight and direction during the recruitment process which culminated with me securing my new role.&#8221; &#8211; Candidate</p>
</article><article class="wikinger-text"><p><strong>Client:</strong> Wikinger Hotdogs</p>
<p><strong>Client Issue:</strong> Major multiples reluctant to take on another supplier in relatively low profile category.</p>
<p><strong>RPM Input: </strong>Tailored category approach, use of both Kantar &amp; retailer specific data, demonstrating incremental benefits from Jars and personally presenting to key customers</p>
<p><strong>Results: </strong>ASDA listing regained, new Tesco listing secured and 2 Wikinger products now in category Top 10.</p>
<p><strong>Testimonial:</strong> &#8220;Richard&#8217;s input has been a key factor in the significant growth of our U.K business and a much more cost-effective option than a full-time overhead.&#8221;</p>
</article></section>
</article>
